folder: Bedford Avenue & Clymer Street, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Bedford Avenue, north side, from Clymer Street to Taylor Street, looking east. At the corner of the former Street is the old First Dutch Reformed Church of Williamsburg, which later became a synagogue. View 2 shows the 3-story house adjoining the church, known as the Cross mansion and owned by Marion Cross, whose father settled in Brooklyn in 1845. View 3 is west from Taylor Street, showing the aforementioned sturctures and the Hebrew High School (right). In the left background is the
Christ Protestant Episcopal Church.
Views 1-3: Eugene L. Armbruster Collection------ View 1: 1923
View 2: 1924
View 3: 1922

View 4; P. L. Sperr ---------------------------April 1[2?], 1941
